d)"},{"pos":[9666,9681],"content":"Escaping Braces","linkify":"Escaping Braces","nodes":[{"content":"Escaping Braces","pos":[0,15]}]},{"content":"Opening and closing braces are interpreted as starting and ending a format item.","pos":[9685,9765]},{"content":"Consequently, you must use an escape sequence to display a literal opening brace or closing brace.","pos":[9766,9864]},{"content":"Specify two opening braces (\"{{\") in the fixed text to display one opening brace (\"{\"), or two closing braces (\"}}\") to display one closing brace (\"}\").","pos":[9865,10017]},{"content":"Braces in a format item are interpreted sequentially in the order they are encountered.","pos":[10018,10105]},{"content":"Interpreting nested braces is not supported.","pos":[10106,10150]},{"content":"The way escaped braces are interpreted can lead to unexpected results.","pos":[10157,10227]},{"content":"For example, consider the format item \"{{{0:D}}}\", which is intended to display an opening brace, a numeric value formatted as a decimal number, and a closing brace.","pos":[10228,10393]},{"content":"However, the format item is actually interpreted in the following manner:","pos":[10394,10467]},{"content":"The first two opening braces (\"{{\") are escaped and yield one opening brace.","pos":[10477,10553]},{"content":"The next three characters (\"{0:\") are interpreted as the start of a format item.","pos":[10563,10643]},{"content":"The next character (\"D\") would be interpreted as the Decimal standard numeric format specifier, but the next two escaped braces (\"}}\") yield a single brace.","pos":[10653,10809]},{"content":"Because the resulting string (\"D}\") is not a standard numeric format specifier, the resulting string is interpreted as a custom format string that means display the literal string \"D}\".","pos":[10810,10995]},{"content":"The last brace (\"}\") is interpreted as the end of the format item.","pos":[11005,11071]},{"content":"The final result that is displayed is the literal string, \"{D}\".","pos":[11081,11145]},{"content":"The numeric value that was to be formatted is not displayed.","pos":[11146,11206]},{"content":"One way to write your code to avoid misinterpreting escaped braces and format items is to format the braces and format item separately.","pos":[11213,11348]},{"content":"That is, in the first format operation display a literal opening brace, in the next operation display the result of the format item, then in the final operation display a literal closing brace.","pos":[11349,11542]},{"content":"The following example illustrates this approach.","pos":[11543,11591]},{"pos":[11598,11855],"content":"[!code-csharp[Formatting.Composite#2](../../../samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_CLR/Formatting.Composite/cs/Escaping1.cs#2)]\n[!code-vb[Formatting.Composite#2](../../../samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_CLR/Formatting.Composite/vb/Escaping1.vb#2)]","leadings":[""," "],"nodes":[{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[!code-csharp</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Formatting.Composite#2<ept id=\"p2\">](../../../samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_CLR/Formatting.Composite/cs/Escaping1.cs#2)</ept><ept id=\"p1\">]</ept>","pos":[0,127],"source":"[!code-csharp[Formatting.Composite#2](../../../samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_CLR/Formatting.Composite/cs/Escaping1.cs#2)]"},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[!code-vb</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Formatting.Composite#2<ept id=\"p2\">](../../../samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_CLR/Formatting.Composite/vb/Escaping1.vb#2)</ept><ept id=\"p1\">]</ept>","pos":[128,256],"source":"[!code-vb[Formatting.Composite#2](../../../samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_CLR/Formatting.Composite/vb/Escaping1.vb#2)]"}]},{"pos":[11865,11881],"content":"Processing Order","linkify":"Processing Order","nodes":[{"content":"Processing Order","pos":[0,16]}]},{"content":"If the call to the composite formatting method includes an <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.IFormatProvider&gt;</ph> argument whose value is not <ph id=\"p